        {
          "content": "{\n  \"files\": [\n    {\"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\", \"path\": \".github/CODEOWNERS\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\", \"path\": \".github/workflows/codeowners-validator.yml\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\", \"path\": \"scripts/codeowners-manifest/index.js\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\", \"path\": \"scripts/codeowners-manifest/generate.js\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\", \"path\": \"scripts/codeowners-manifest/raw.js\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\", \"path\": \"scripts/codeowners-manifest/metadata.js\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\", \"path\": \"scripts/codeowners-manifest/constants.js\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\", \"path\": \"scripts/codeowners-manifest/README.md\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\", \"path\": \"pkg/services/featuremgmt/codeowners.go\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\", \"path\": \"jest.config.codeowner.js\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\", \"path\": \"scripts/test-coverage-by-codeowner.js\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\", \"path\": \"package.json\"}\n  ],\n  \"symbols\": [\n    {\"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\", \"path\": \"pkg/services/featuremgmt/codeowners.go\", \"symbol\": \"codeowner\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\", \"path\": \"scripts/codeowners-manifest/index.js\", \"symbol\": \"generateCodeownersManifestComplete\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\", \"path\": \"scripts/codeowners-manifest/generate.js\", \"symbol\": \"generateCodeownersManifest\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\", \"path\": \"scripts/codeowners-manifest/raw.js\", \"symbol\": \"generateCodeownersRawAudit\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\", \"path\": \"scripts/codeowners-manifest/metadata.js\", \"symbol\": \"generateCodeownersMetadata\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"grafana/grafana\", \"path\": \"scripts/test-coverage-by-codeowner.js\", \"symbol\": \"runTestCoverageByCodeowner\"}\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"The CODEOWNERS infrastructure in grafana/grafana comprises a multi-layered system for managing code ownership and enabling team-based analytics:\\n\\n1. **GitHub CODEOWNERS Definition** (.github/CODEOWNERS): The authoritative ownership file that maps repository paths to GitHub teams and users, defining which teams own specific codebases.\\n\\n2. **Validation Workflow** (.github/workflows/codeowners-validator.yml): A GitHub Actions workflow that runs on pull requests to the main branch, using the mszostok/codeowners-validator action to validate the CODEOWNERS file against checks for files, duplicate patterns, and syntax.\\n\\n3. **Manifest Generation Infrastructure** (scripts/codeowners-manifest/): A comprehensive JavaScript-based tooling suite that parses the CODEOWNERS file and generates structured manifests:\\n   - index.js: Main orchestrator that coordinates the complete manifest generation workflow with caching via metadata.json\\n   - raw.js: Generates raw audit data (JSONL format) by spawning the yarn github-codeowners CLI tool\\n   - generate.js: Processes raw audit data to produce three key manifest files: teams.json (unique teams), teams-by-filename.json (files mapped to owners), and filenames-by-team.json (files grouped by team)\\n   - metadata.js: Creates metadata with SHA-256 hashes of the CODEOWNERS file and repository files to enable intelligent caching\\n   - constants.js: Centralizes all file path configuration for manifest outputs\\n\\n4. **Feature Management Type** (pkg/services/featuremgmt/codeowners.go): Defines the `codeowner` string type in Go for feature flag management, including constants mapping named codeowner strings (e.g., grafanaAppPlatformSquad, grafanaBackendServicesSquad) to their GitHub team format (e.g., @grafana/grafana-app-platform-squad). These enable feature flags scoped to specific teams.\\n\\n5. **npm Script Orchestration** (package.json): Provides user-facing commands:\\n   - \\\"codeowners-manifest\\\": Main entry point that coordinates the complete pipeline\\n   - \\\"codeowners-manifest:clean\\\": Cleans the manifest directory\\n   - \\\"codeowners-manifest:generate\\\": Generates manifest files from raw audit\\n   - \\\"codeowners-manifest:metadata\\\": Generates metadata for caching\\n   - \\\"codeowners-manifest:raw\\\": Generates raw audit data\\n   - \\\"test:coverage:by-codeowner\\\": Runs test coverage analysis by team\\n\\n6. **Test Coverage Integration** (jest.config.codeowner.js, scripts/test-coverage-by-codeowner.js): Enables running tests and measuring coverage for specific teams by filtering source and test files from the codeowners manifest. The jest config uses the TEAM_NAME environment variable and filenames-by-team.json to run coverage reports specific to team ownership.\\n\\nThis infrastructure enables Grafana to maintain clear code ownership across a large monorepo, validate CODEOWNERS integrity in CI/CD, track coverage metrics by team responsibility, and manage feature flags scoped to specific teams.\"\n}\n",
